### Configuration
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@companyId = REPLACE_WITH_ID_FROM_GET_ALL

### 1. Create or Verify a Company
# Uses 'upsert' logic: creates if name is new, updates if name exists
POST {{baseUrl}}/companies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "SecureCorp India",
  "email": "contact@securecorp.in",
  "scope": "External Web Application Pentest",
  "contactInfo": "VAPT Team - Ext 402",
  "logoUrl": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/vapt-assets/logos/securecorp.png"
}


### 2. List All Registered Companies
# Includes a count of projects associated with each company
GET {{baseUrl}}/companies


### 3. Get Specific Company Details
# Useful for the Client Profile page in your dashboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/companies/{{companyId}}


### 4. Update Company Profile
# Tests the PATCH logic for changing contact details or scope
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/companies/{{companyId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contactInfo": "Global Security Operations Center",
  "scope": "Full Infrastructure & Web Audit"
}


### 5. Delete a Company
# Note: Will fail with 400 if active projects are linked
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/companies/{{companyId}}